inviting conversations expanding views of africa events at stanford inviting conversations expanding views of africa facebook twitter email print add to calendar the arts of africa date from the beginning of humanity to the present and express universal and timeless ideas the newly reinstalled african art galleries feature more than 200 objects and are designed to expand conventional ways of considering african art and culture the galleries offer historical depth geographic and chronological representation ranging from the contemporary times to ancient egypt and a diverse range of media sundays in september the african galleries feature center docents conducting informal discussions about the new installation inviting conversations are not formal tours but rather casual discussions about art and are offered to museum visitors on a drop in basis between 11 30 am and 1 30 pm in the galleries when ongoing every week from september 4 2011 through september 25 2011 11 30 am approximate duration of 2 hour s where cantor arts center just off palm drive at museum way and lomita drive map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students members tags tour international arts contact 723 3469 admission open wed sun 11am 5pm thursdays until 8pm admission is free closed monday and tuesday permalink http events stanford edu events 285 28583 more info last modified august 30 2011
